	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=/db/item.html?item=11406&mid=105501386734929>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=/db/item.html?item=11406&mid=105501386734929>Reason...</a> <a id=fs8 href=/db/item.html?item=11406&mid=105501386734929#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Sat, Jun 7th 4:04 PM 2003</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=174116><span id= >Branaddar</span></a><br><span id=notbold>481 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [4.36]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>The reason Lord Seru has this amazing weapon that is none/none is not for fancy show or anything of the like.<br><br>The game engine only allows NPCs to do a certain amount of damage in melee combat.<br><br>This sword allows Seru to break that cap, by having the humanoid bane damage, the insane dmg/dly, the 1hs skill modifier, the cold damage.<br><br>It might be part of a quest, since lore has it that the Combine Empire was working on a Sword of Truth, which would be capable of killing the Sleeper, and they did revamp ST after Luclin came out, but I'm pretty sure it's just to break the melee cap, and they threw in the background lore to the weapon as well.</p>&nbsp;<br><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br><a href=HTTP://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=939819 target=akztarg><span style='color: red;'><b>Bransback Balefire</b></span style='color: red;'></a><br>Monk of <span style='color: green;'>Invictvs</span style='color: green;'><br><span style='color: blue;'>Tholuxe Paells</span style='color: blue;'></td></tr>
	     <tr><td colspan=2 align=right class=mform id=fs8>1 Reply</td></tr>
